  "text": "The mean ascending aorta diameters measured at the pulmonary artery bifurcation level were 36.7 ± 3.5 mm for males and 33.9 ± 3.3 mm for females. These values are similar to those reported by Kalsch et al [CITATION_1] (37.1 ± 4 mm for males and 34.5 ± 4 mm for females), while they were slightly greater than those reported by Wolak et al [CITATION_2] (33.5 ± 4 mm for males and 31.4 ± 3 mm for females). These differences may be due to differences in the study populations, CT scan protocol, and measurement approach.",
